# Example .npmrc for Render or other CI when you need to authenticate to private
# registries. Do NOT commit real tokens — set them in your Render service ENV vars
# and reference them here, or add the file via Render's dashboard.

# Use an npm token stored in the environment (RENDER_NPM_TOKEN or NPM_TOKEN)
//registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}

# If you use a private GitHub Packages registry, example:
@my-org:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com/
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}
